spans.text: from the dark-rolling of the lake
like the gold of the stranger
like a blast from the desert
thou first of the maids of Lutha
the music of departed bards in the dream of thy rest
grief when peace dwells in the breast of the sad
the mournful , OH daughter of Toscar
after the mildew has passed over it
I raised my sails , and rushed into the bay of Croma
a staff , on which the warrior leaned
his aged hand and blessed the son of Fingal
the hero , the strength of Crothar's arm has failed
the hero , the strength of Crothar's arm
my arm the bossy shield of Calthar , whom the hero had slain in war
he seels it with his aged hands
not like the king of Morven
Let the feast of my halls
let my bards raise the song
a sigh , that darkly dwelled in every breast
that my arms were fixed in the hall
the disordered steps of his father
my father , to feel the strength of my arm
IT is not time to fill the shell
they poured forth their burning souls , and the harp answered to their voice
my voice for Fovar-gormo , when they laid the chief in earth
, my son has not fallen without his fame
